HEADWORD: luge
<hw>luge</hw> <pr>(l⟦oomac⟧zh)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>a racing sled
for one or two people; it is raced down a chute of packed snow or ice,
and the occupant(s) lie down on it with feet in the direction of
motion.</def>⟦br⟧
